Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil; cover and cook until almost tender. Drain and cool. In a large bowl, combine soup, 1-1/2 cups cheese, sour cream, onions, salt and pepper; stir in potatoes. Place in a greased 13-in. x 9-in.x 2-in. baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 25-30 minutes or until heated through.